item.title: First time compiling, over 100 errors
item.dc:creator: @matzie matzie
item.description:
@matzie wrote:

[quote=“The Web Guy, post:5, topic:544706”][quote author=beast14 link=topic=663583.msg4434770#msg4434770 date=1404699490]
your missing a } at the end of the new thing u added
[/quote]

That’s not always what 100 errors is…

HcoJustin and Camballer are correct, in your compiler.bat when you click edit, make sure all of the directories are being referenced so that they are compiled correctly. If you’re not sure what we mean, just use a compiler generator.[/quote]
There is no need for a compiler generator in most servers. Unless it is a plugin based one, at which case the server and the plugins are developed separately.

public class Foo { public static void main(String[] args) { new Bar(); } } }

public class Bar { }
javac Foo.java will compile both Foo and Bar
It will auto-compile most dependencies. At least it did for me (:

Read full topic
